<p><strong>Helen<br /></strong>So the phrase done and dusted means work on something is completely finished. When I heard you say dust, I thought you were asking me if I had cleaned the house. No way, I only got the keys yesterday! I haven't even set foot in the house yet.</p> 
<p><strong>Neil<br /></strong>Done and dusted is actually a very common expression. We hear it a lot at work. And usually it means something has been completed successfully, there's no more work to be done on it. Let's hear some examples.</p> 
<p><strong>Examples<br /></strong></p> 
<p><em>The dispute between me and the council about my parking ticket has been resolved. It's done and dusted.</em></p> 
