<p><strong>Neil<br /></strong>Hello and welcome to The English We Speak with me Neil…</p> 
<p><strong>Li<br /></strong>…and me Li. Hello.</p> 
<p><strong>Neil<br /></strong>In this programme, we're talking about clothes.</p> 
<p><strong>Li<br /></strong>Clothes! Oh My favourite subject in the whole world! I know all the designers, I try different styles… I love clothes! Let's talk about MY clothes.</p> 
<p><strong>Neil<br /></strong>Well… actually I thought we should talk about our smalls.</p> 
<p><strong>Li<br /></strong>Smalls?! Do you think my clothes are too small for me? Are you calling me fat?</p> 
<p><strong>Neil<br /></strong>No, Li. You look fine. 'Smalls' is a word we use for underwear.</p> 
<p><strong>Li<br /></strong>Smalls. So you are talking about women's knickers and men's underpants, socks, women's bras…</p> 
<p><strong>Neil<br /></strong>Yes. And we can refer to our underwear as 'smalls' or 'undies'.</p> 
<p><strong>Li<br /></strong>Undies. That's easy to remember because it refers to what we wear under our clothes – undies.</p> 
<p><strong>Neil<br /></strong>Two easy words to remember when you talk about underwear. And remember they are always plural.</p> 
<p><strong>Li<br /></strong>I see. So you don't say 'one small' or one 'undy'.</p> 
<p><strong>Neil<br /></strong>No, you don't. Smalls and undies are always used in the plural and they mean underwear. Now let's hear some examples of how these words are used.</p> 
<p><strong>Examples<br /></strong>Linda, hurry up or we'll miss the plane! Don't forget to pack your smalls!</p> 
<p>Billy, don't walk around the house in your undies. Your granny is coming to visit and she'll be here at any time.</p> 
<p><strong>Neil<br /></strong>Now don't forget that these words for underwear are very informal and British slang.</p> 
<p><strong>Li<br /></strong>Well, smalls and undies can look good too, even if not many people will see them.</p> 
<p><strong>Neil<br /></strong>So you want to talk about fashion now.</p> 
<p><strong>Li<br /></strong>Of course. I love fashion! Do you love fashion, Neil?</p> 
