<p><strong>Examples<br /></strong>A: Did you find any good deals?<br />B: No, <strong>not a sausage</strong>.&nbsp;</p> 
<p>A: Did the boss say anything about my project?<br />B: No, sorry, <strong>not a sausage</strong>.&nbsp;</p> 
<p>A: Are there any sandwiches left?<br />B: I'm afraid not. <strong>Not a sausage</strong>.&nbsp;</p> 
<p><strong>Feifei<br /></strong>That last one might have sounded confusing: No sandwiches left?&nbsp;</p> 
<p><strong>Neil<br /></strong><strong>Not a sausage</strong>! Yes, confusingly, we were asking about another kind of food – and the answer was still <strong>not a sausage</strong>.&nbsp;</p> 
