<p><strong>Rob<br /></strong>Right, lovely, OK, that's better. I've had a nice cup of coffee and I'm ready to explain the meaning for today's The English We Speak. So, here you go. When you are 'on the ball', it means you are alert and quick to react to things.&nbsp;</p> 
<p><strong>Li<br /></strong>It comes from sports, doesn't it?&nbsp;</p> 
<p><strong>Rob<br /></strong>Yes. And there's another phrase: 'to keep your eye on the ball' which has a very similar meaning.<strong>&nbsp;</strong></p> 
